In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 17, 2010, as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23, 2010, as Constitution Week. He highlights the importance of the Constitution and its role in guiding the nation through times of peace and conflict. The President emphasizes the significance of citizenship and encourages individuals to participate in democracy. He acknowledges the new American citizens who commemorate Constitution Day by taking an oath to support and defend the Constitution. President Obama calls on federal, state, and local officials, as well as civic, social, and educational organizations, to conduct ceremonies and programs that recognize the Constitution and reaffirm the rights and obligations of citizens.